overview: The user wanted to elevate the visual appeal of their sleep
  questionnaire app from a generic look to a more calming and professional
  aesthetic. I initiated a comprehensive overhaul, starting with a new
  sleep-themed color palette and custom utility classes. Key components like the
  main form layout, progress bar, and intro section were redesigned with subtle
  background effects, improved visual hierarchy, and interactive elements. All
  UI components, including checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders, received a
  polished look with enhanced hover and selected states. I systematically
  applied this consistent theming across all questionnaire sections, replacing
  old gray boxes with refined card-style groupings. Additionally, I debugged and
  fixed a console error where input fields were receiving null values. The
  outcome is a significantly more cohesive and aesthetically pleasing
  application, with further refinements planned for alert colors and section
  border opacities.
